    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "Rear hub bearing unit removal and installation"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "1. Hub Bearing Unit Development"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "672_3.0_jpn_11035778_3.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "1. Lift Set",
      "refs": [
        {
          "id": "G000319",
          "label": "Lift Set",
          "resolved": true
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "2. Rear wheel removal",
      "refs": [
        {
          "id": "R000659",
          "label": "Rear wheel removal",
          "resolved": true
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "3. Parking brake release"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "4. Brake drum removal",
      "refs": [
        {
          "id": "R000695",
          "label": "Brake drum removal",
          "resolved": true
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "5. Rear wheel sensor removal",
      "refs": [
        {
          "id": "R000715",
          "label": "Rear wheel sensor removal",
          "resolved": true
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Do not disconnect the wheel sensor cord."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "6. Spindle nut removal"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "672_3.0_jpn_11035779_3.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Caulk (B) the spindle nut (A) and remove it. Replace the spindle nut with a new one at the time of installation."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "7. Rear hub bearing unit removal"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "672_3.0_jpn_11035780_3.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Remove the hub bearing unit (A)."
    },
    {
      "type": "attention",
      "items": [
        "Note that if the bearing unit is pulled strongly outward, the roller of the inboard joint of the drive shaft will be pulled out.",
        "Be very careful not to bend the brake pipe.",
        "When installing, replace the mounting bolts (B) of the hub bearing unit with new ones."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "8. Installation Precautions"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Pay attention to the following items and install in the reverse order of removal."
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": false,
      "items": [
        {
          "text": "Apply a small amount of engine oil to the nut seat surface before installation, and caulk the spindle nut after tightening to the specified torque."
        },
        {
          "text": "Apply a small amount of engine oil to the nut seat surface before installation, and caulk the spindle nut after tightening to the specified torque."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "9. Wheel alignment Inspection and adjustment",
      "refs": [
        {
          "id": "R000655",
          "label": "Wheel alignment Inspection and adjustment",
          "resolved": true
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "10. VSA sensor Midpoint write",
      "refs": [
        {
          "id": "R000714",
          "label": "VSA sensor Midpoint write",
          "resolved": true
        }
      ]
    }
  ],
